article.headline: Utes enjoy 43-22 rebounding edge
article.story:
FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. (AP) -- Kim Smith went 3-for-3 from 3-point
range and scored 15 points to lead four Utah players in double
figures, and the 23rd-ranked Utes beat Northern Arizona 69-45
Sunday.

Utah took control of the game by opening the second half with a
15-6 spurt to take a 43-24 lead with 15:25 left.

The Utes (8-3) led 28-18 at halftime. It was a sloppy first half
in which the teams combined for 31 turnovers.

Carley Marshall and Kelsy Stireman each had 13 points for Utah.

Alyssa Wahl scored 16 points to lead the Lumberjacks (5-3), and
Natalie Metz added eight points and nine rebounds.
